summary:
Chapter 34 came out yesterday!

 Be My Prize Poe Dameron/Kylo Ren, Poe Dameron/Finn Poe Dameron is forced to take a vacation and...
body:
Chapter 34 came out yesterday!

Be My Prize

Poe Dameron/Kylo Ren, Poe Dameron/Finn

Poe Dameron is forced to take a vacation and has to leave the Resistance base, and he is not exactly thrilled about it. He soon meets a stranger, who is the definition of “tall, dark, and handsome”, and they are both fascinated with each other. The vacation is suddenly starting to seem less and less like a bore.

However, things can only go downhill from here, when one of the interested parties is a Resistance pilot and the other hails the flag of the First Order.

—

The story starts before the events of The Force Awakens and continues past the the movie.

The fic will update every Saturday until I run out of my buffer, though I will attempt to continue the weekly schedule even after that happens.

summary: I went to a May the Fourth party where I was one of two women in a roomful of fanboys. During TFA there was a lot of joking...
body:
I went to a May the Fourth party where I was one of two women in a roomful of fanboys. During TFA there was a lot of joking around and not taking anything srsly. We got to the scene where Rey’s been captured and Kylo is creepily intimidating her by getting in her personal space. Tons of jokes here about Kylo being too emo for his shirt, leaning hard into the kidnapper vibe, etc.

When Kylo tries to read Rey’s mind and she turns his own powers on him, the only guy who hadn’t yet seen the movie yelled, “You idiot! Everyone knows girl Jedi are stronger! What a moron.”

It was such a sincere moment of frustration. Like, this dude didn’t just get it, he assumed we all got it, that it was canon from the moment Leia stepped out as a Skywalker that female Jedi are deadly af. That’s gotten me through a couple things tbh.

blog.name: unspeakablehorror
blog.title: Loftwings and Demons
blog.description:
I post about Legend of Zelda and Star Wars. Especially Skyward Sword and my rather longish fanfic Ascent (on fanfiction.net and AO3). I am a fanatical Ghirahim fan, in case you hadn't noticed. My favorite Star Wars villain is General Grievous, and my Cut Strings fanfic features him as a central character.


I'll probably also have posts on writing and random posts on things that that I find interesting or important. Please feel free to send me notes if you want to talk!


This blog is rated PG-13 (or as close to that as you're likely to find on Tumblr, anyway). Is that SFW? That depends on the number of below-13 people hanging out at your workplace, I imagine.


Rabbits.


ETA Dec 23,2018: Had to make some changes to my blog theme for SSL compatibility reasons.
